\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Quick Start Tutorial:
 Discord Computer Olympiad Interface with GTP
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This quick tutorial introduces the use of the Discord Computer Olympiad Interface (DCOI) to perform automatic matches on Discord using the GTP protocol to communicate with your program.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This document assumes that you already have a Discord account and know how to use the basic features of Discord (joining a server,
 channel,
 accessing settings).
 If not,
 or more generally if you need more detailed instructions,
 please consult the User Guide,
 which will also introduce you to 
\series bold
advanced features
\series default
,
 
\series bold
tips
\series default
,
 and 
\series bold
common mistakes
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Creating a “bot account”
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The first step is to create a “bot account,” that is,
 to create a Discord application with the options required to have a functional bot in the DCOI context.
 This allows the bot to interact in Discord conversations.
 If you find these initial steps too complicated,
 we can lend you a bot account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The steps to create a bot account are as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Create a 
\series bold
new application
\series default
 on the Discord website:
 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

https://discord.com/developers/applications
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
If you have any problems,
 try a different internet browser.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Enable
\series default
 the “
\series bold
Message Content Intent
\series default
” option in the “Bot” tab.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Retrieve the bot TOKEN (
\series bold
Reset Token
\series default
 button):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
copy and paste
\series default
 the token as the value of 
\series bold
PLAYER_BOT_DISCORD_TOKEN
\series default
 in the file 
\series bold
parameters.conf
\series default
 (in the discord_interface folder).
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Never share the token —
 it is the password of your bot (sensitive information).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
In the “
\series bold
OAuth2
\series default
” 
\series bold
tab
\series default
,
 under “OAuth2 URL Generator,” 
\series bold
check
\series default
 the “
\series bold
bot
\series default
” option.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
In the “
\series bold
bot permissions
\series default
” subsection,
 check the following:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
View Channels
\series default
,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Send Messages
\series default
,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Read Message History
\series default
,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Add Reactions
\series default
.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Send
\series default
 the URL located at the bottom of the page (in the “
\series bold
Generated URL
\series default
” section) to the organizer so that they can invite your bot to the server.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Back in Discord (optional but strongly recommended):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
In 
\series bold
Settings
\series default
 (gear icon at the bottom left),
 “
\series bold
Advanced
\series default
” tab:
 
\series bold
enable
\series default
 “
\series bold
Developer Mode
\series default
”.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Close the settings window.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Click on 
\series bold
your name
\series default
 at the bottom left,
 then click “
\series bold
Copy ID
\series default
”.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Paste this value into the 
\series bold
parameters.conf
\series default
 file as the value for 
\series bold
OWNER_ID
\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Section
Installation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a terminal,
 run (prerequisites:
 Python 3.10+) :
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
cd discord_interface 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
(optional but recommanded):
 activate a Python virtual environment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
chmod +x install.sh
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
source install.sh
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
(optional) Test the installation:
 run the following in the terminal:
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

python3 test_installation.py
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
GTP Command Specification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Table 1 briefly describes how to implement in your program the execution of the GTP commands required by the Discord bot for communication.
 Since GTP communication occurs through standard output,
 we recommend not using it for any other purpose (such as debugging,
 etc.).
\end_layout

