\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
List of GTP commands to implement,
 the syntax of their return and their expected effect (<move> is an action in text format (A1,
 A2-B3,
 ...,
 see the syntax in the User Guide) ;
 <player> is an integer 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

 ;
 <game> is the game name of the match).
 Remark:
 commands 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

game
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

player
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 are not part of standard GTP ;
 they are optional (make them only return 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

=
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

) ;
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

game
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is required only for multi-games participation ;
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

player
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is required only for profiling (see User Guide).
 Remark:
 each return starts with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

=
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "tab:List-of-GTP-commands"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Running Your Bot
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Edit the text file 
\series bold
parameters.conf
\series default
,
 specifying the following attributes for your program:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
program_name
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
program_arguments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
program_directory
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Optionally,
 program test:
 verifying the GTP command specification:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
run in the terminal:
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

python3 test_gtp_ai_from_conf.py
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Then run in terminal:
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

python3 main_gtp_ai_from_conf.py
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 to launch your bot.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Running a Match
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Join the competition’s Discord server:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
beta test serveur:
 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

https://discord.gg/mbHBdH3K
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
competition serveur:
 coming soon (T.B.A.)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Join one of the match channels of the Discord serveur.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
You,
 your opponent,
 or an organizer must execute the following commands in the Discord conversation:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Specify the game using the command 
\series bold
!set game 
\shape italic
GAME_NAME
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
if needed:
 
\series bold
!available_games
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\align block
Start the match with the command 
\series bold
!start 
\shape italic
PLAYER_1
\shape default
 
\shape italic
PLAYER_2
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\align block
For each 
\shape italic
PLAYER_i
\shape default
,
 write 
\series bold

\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

@
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\series default
 then select the corresponding player or bot from the list and confirm by pressing “Enter”.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\align block
If it doesn’t appear in the list,
 start typing its name.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Simply typing the name is not enough —
 you must select it and press “Enter.”
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\end_deeper
